## 1. Color Tokens

### 1.1 Semantic CSS Variables (Design Tokens)

These are the primary tokens to use when wiring components to Figma. They map to Figma Local Variables.

| CSS Variable | Role | Default Palette |
|---|---|---|
| `--ui-primary` | Primary brand color (500 step) | Green (#00C16A) |
| `--ui-primary-50` … `--ui-primary-950` | Full primary scale | Green scale |
| `--ui-secondary` | Secondary brand color | Blue (#2B7FFF) |
| `--ui-secondary-50` … `--ui-secondary-950` | Full secondary scale | Blue scale |
| `--ui-success` | Success state | Green (#00C16A) |
| `--ui-success-50` … `--ui-success-950` | Full success scale | Green scale |
| `--ui-info` | Informational state | Blue (#2B7FFF) |
| `--ui-info-50` … `--ui-info-950` | Full info scale | Blue scale |
| `--ui-warning` | Warning state | Yellow (#FCC800) |
| `--ui-warning-50` … `--ui-warning-950` | Full warning scale | Yellow scale |
| `--ui-error` | Error/danger state | Red (#FB2C36) |
| `--ui-error-50` … `--ui-error-950` | Full error scale | Red scale |
| `--ui-neutral` | Neutral/gray base | Slate scale |
| `--ui-neutral-50` … `--ui-neutral-950` | Full neutral scale | Slate scale |
| `--ui-bg` | Page background | `--ui-neutral-50` (light) / `--ui-neutral-950` (dark) |
| `--ui-bg-elevated` | Elevated surface (cards, popovers) | white / `--ui-neutral-900` |
| `--ui-bg-accented` | Accented surface | `--ui-neutral-100` / `--ui-neutral-800` |
| `--ui-bg-inverted` | Inverted background | `--ui-neutral-900` / white |
| `--ui-text-highlighted` | Headings / high-emphasis text | `--ui-neutral-900` / white |
| `--ui-text` | Body text | `--ui-neutral-700` / `--ui-neutral-200` |
| `--ui-text-muted` | Muted/secondary text | `--ui-neutral-500` |
| `--ui-text-dimmed` | Very low-emphasis text | `--ui-neutral-400` |
| `--ui-text-inverted` | Text on inverted background | white / `--ui-neutral-900` |
| `--ui-border` | Default border | `--ui-neutral-200` / `--ui-neutral-800` |
