## 2. Border Radius Tokens

Nuxt UI v4 exposes a configurable radius via a single `--ui-radius` base variable. All component radii derive from it.

| CSS Variable | Default Value | Usage |
|---|---|---|
| `--ui-radius` | `0.375rem` (6px) | Base radius — controls all components |
| `--ui-radius-sm` | `calc(var(--ui-radius) - 2px)` | Small elements: badges, chips |
| `--ui-radius-md` | `var(--ui-radius)` | Default: buttons, inputs, selects |
| `--ui-radius-lg` | `calc(var(--ui-radius) + 2px)` | Cards, modals, drawers |
| `--ui-radius-xl` | `calc(var(--ui-radius) + 4px)` | Large panels |
| `--ui-radius-2xl` | `calc(var(--ui-radius) + 8px)` | Extra large surfaces |
| `--ui-radius-full` | `9999px` | Pills, circular avatars |

**Figma Presets — Border Radius (Figma page `1960:8749`):**

The Design Kit ships two border-radius preset tables:
- **Default** — `none` / `sm(2px)` / `md(4px)` / `lg(6px)` / `xl(8px)` / `2xl(12px)` / `full`
- **Rounded** — same scale with rounder base (e.g. base = 8px)

